  <div class="container">
    <h1>API Documentation</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Integrate SponsorForm with your existing workflows</p>

    <h2>Authentication</h2>
    <p>All API requests require authentication using a Bearer token. Get your token by logging in and copying it from your account settings.</p>
    
    <pre><code>Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_TOKEN</code></pre>

    <h2>Endpoints</h2>

    <h3>List Your Forms</h3>
    <div class="endpoint">
      <span class="method">GET</span>
      <span class="url">/api/forms</span>
    </div>
    <p>Returns a list of all forms created by your account.</p>
    
    <pre><code>{
  "forms": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Q1 2026 Sponsors",
      "slug": "a3f7b2d9",
      "created_at": "2026-02-21T10:00:00.000Z"
    }
  ]
}</code></pre>

    <h3>Get Form Submissions</h3>
    <div class="endpoint">
      <span class="method">GET</span>
      <span class="url">/api/submissions?form_id=123</span>
    </div>
    <p>Retrieve all submissions for a specific form as JSON.</p>
    
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Parameter</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Required</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>form_id</td>
        <td>integer</td>
        <td>Yes</td>
        <td>The ID of your form</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <pre><code>{
  "form": {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Q1 2026 Sponsors",
    "slug": "a3f7b2d9"
  },
  "submissions": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "data": {
        "company_name": "Acme Corp",
        "contact_email": "sponsor@acme.com",
        "logo_url": "https://acme.com/logo.png",
        "ad_copy": "Check out Acme Corp for all your..."
      },
      "created_at": "2026-02-21T15:30:00.000Z"
    }
  ]
}</code></pre>

    <h2>Webhooks (Pro)</h2>
    <p>Pro users can configure webhook URLs for their forms. When a sponsor submits the form, we'll POST the data to your webhook endpoint.</p>
    
    <div class="note">
      <strong>Note:</strong> Webhooks are only available on the Pro plan ($9/month).
    </div>

    <h3>Webhook Payload</h3>
    <pre><code>{
  "form_id": 1,
  "data": {
    "company_name": "Acme Corp",
    "contact_email": "sponsor@acme.com",
    "logo_url": "https://acme.com/logo.png",
    "ad_copy": "Check out Acme Corp..."
  },
  "timestamp": "2026-02-21T15:30:00.000Z"
}</code></pre>

    <h3>Setting Up Webhooks</h3>
    <ol style="margin: 20px 0; padding-left: 30px;">
      <li>Create or edit a form</li>
      <li>Enter your webhook URL in the "Webhook URL" field</li>
      <li>We'll send a POST request to that URL for every new submission</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Example: cURL</h2>
    <pre><code># Get your forms
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
  https://your-domain.com/api/forms

# Get submissions for a form
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
  "https://your-domain.com/api/submissions?form_id=1"</code></pre>

    <h2>Example: JavaScript</h2>
    <pre><code>const response = await fetch('/api/submissions?form_id=1', {
  headers: {
    'Authorization': 'Bearer YOUR_API_TOKEN'
  }
});

const { submissions } = await response.json();
console.log(submissions);</code></pre>

    <h2>Rate Limits</h2>
    <p>API requests are limited to 100 requests per minute per account.</p>

